com.emitrom.flash4j.core.client.utils

Interface IDataOutput

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ByteArray, IoClass, Socket, URLStream

    public interface IDataOutput
    The IDataOutput interface provides a set of methods for writing binary data. This interface is the I/O counterpart to the IDataInput interface, which reads binary data.

    The IDataOutput interface is implemented by the FileStream, Socket and ByteArray classes. All IDataInput and IDataOutput operations are "bigEndian" by default (the most significant byte in the sequence is stored at the lowest or first storage address), and are nonblocking.
